<DIV class=3Dpadding10>
<H1>Publications</H1>
<P>Organizations in all sectors of the economy depend upon information =
systems=20
and communications networks, and share common requirements to protect =
sensitive=20
information. ITL works with industry and government to establish secure=20
information technology systems for protecting the integrity, =
confidentiality,=20
reliability, and availability of information.</P>
<P>Under FISMA Act of 2002, the Computer Security Division of the =
Information=20
Technology Laboratory (ITL) develops computer security prototypes, =
tests,=20
standards, and procedures to protect sensitive information from =
unauthorized=20
access or modification. Focus areas include cryptographic technology and =

applications, advanced authentication, public key infrastructure,=20
internetworking security, criteria and assurance, and security =
management and=20
support.</P>
<P>These publications present the results of NIST studies, =
investigations, and=20
research on information technology security issues.</P>
<P>The publications are issued as Special Publications (Spec. Pubs.), =
NISTIRs=20
(Internal Reports), and ITL (formerly CSL) Bulletins. Special =
Publications=20
series include the Spec. Pub. 500 series (Information Technology) and =
the Spec.=20
Pub. 800 series (Computer Security). Computer security-related Federal=20
Information Processing Standards (FIPS) are also =
included.</P></DIV></DIV></DIV><!-- PAGE FOOTER STARTS HERE: INFO, =
